entry.title: The Export (Penalty) (Amendment) Regulations 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Export (Penalty) Regulations 2003 (S.I. 2003/3102, “the 2003 Regulations”). The 2003 Regulations provide that, where a person of a prescribed description contravenes one of the rules listed in the Schedule, that person is liable to a penalty in the prescribed amount.

entry.title: The Student Fees (Amounts) (Amendment) (No. 2) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Student Fees (Amounts) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005 (“the 2005 Regulations”) by increasing the basic and higher amounts prescribed in the 2005 Regulations. The amendments come into operation on 1st September 2012.

entry.title: The Further Education Teachers’ (Eligibility) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Further Education Teachers’ (Eligibility) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2007 (“the 2007 Regulations”).

entry.title: The Income Tax (Manufactured Overseas Dividends) (Amendment No. 2) Regulations 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Income Tax (Manufactured Overseas Dividends) Regulations 1993 (S.I. 1993/2004) (“the principal Regulations”).

entry.title: The Motor Vehicles (Driving Licences) (Amendment) Regulations 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations implement the minimum standards of medical fitness required for diabetes mellitus (“diabetes”), as specified in Directive 2009/112/EC of 25 August 2009 and Directive 2009/113/EC of 25 August 2009 (“the Medical Directives”) (O.J. No. L 223, 26.8.09, p.26 and p.31) which amend respectively Directive 91/439/EEC of the European Parliament and of the Council on driving licences (O.J. No. L 237, 24.8.91, p.1) and Directive 2006/126 EC of the European Parliament and of the Council on driving licences (O.J. No. L 51, 22.2.06, p.17). The Medical Directives were added to Annex XIII of the European Economic Area Agreement by Decision of the EEA Joint Committee No. 28/2010 of 12 March 2010 (O.J. No. L 143, 10.6.10, p.23).

entry.title: The National Health Service Superannuation Scheme etc. (Miscellaneous Amendments) (Scotland) Regulations 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the National Health Service Superannuation Scheme (Scotland) Regulations 2011, the National Health Service Pension Scheme (Scotland) Regulations 2008, the National Health Service (Scotland) (Injury Benefits) Regulations 1998, the National Health Service Superannuation Scheme (Scotland) (Additional Voluntary Contributions) Regulations 1998 and the National Health Service (Compensation for Premature Retirement) (Scotland) Regulations 2003.

entry.title: The Social Security (Work-focused Interviews for Lone Parents and Partners) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend a number of Regulations relating to the requirement for certain benefit recipients to take part in work-focused interviews. These include:

entry.title: The Cirencester Tertiary College Sixth Form College Corporation Designation (England) Order 2011
entry.summary: Section 33B of the Further and Higher Education Act 1992 (“the Act”) makes provision for the body corporate of a further education corporation, or those bodies corporate established by an order under section 143(4) of the Learning and Skills Act 2000 in respect of an institution in England, to apply to be designated as a sixth form college corporation.

entry.title: The Debt Relief Orders (Designation of Competent Authorities) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations are made under Article 208U (approved intermediaries) of the Insolvency (Northern Ireland) Order 1989. Article 208U was inserted into that Order by the Debt Relief Act (Northern Ireland) 2010.

title.div: The Protection from Tobacco (Sales from Vending Machines) (Wales) Regulations 2011 / Rheoliadau Amddiffyn rhag Tybaco (Gwerthiannau o Beiriannau Gwerthu) (Cymru) 2011

div.p: These Regulations prohibit the sale of tobacco from an automatic machine.
Mae'r Rheoliadau hyn yn gwahardd gwerthu tybaco o beiriant awtomatig.

entry.title: The M1/Trunk Road T3 (Motorway Service Area) Order (Northern Ireland) 2011
entry.summary: This Order provides that 439 metres of new slip roads described in the Schedule and more particularly delineated and coloured red on the map shall be special roads subject to motorway traffic restrictions and be part of the Belfast-Ballygawley-Londonderry-Land Frontier Trunk Road T3.

entry.title: The Designation of Schools having a Religious Character (England) Order 2011
entry.summary: This Order designates the voluntary schools named in the Order as having a religious character in accordance with section 69(3) of the School Standards and Framework Act 1998 (“the Act”).

entry.title: The Prostitution (Public Places) (Scotland) Act 2007 (Disqualification from Driving) Order 2011
entry.summary: This Order makes provision which is consequential on the Prostitution (Public Places) (Scotland) Act 2007 (“the 2007 Act”).

entry.title: The Immigration (Designation of Travel Bans) (Amendment No.6) Order 2011
entry.summary: This Order amends the Immigration (Designation of Travel Bans) Order 2000 (“the 2000 Order”) by substituting the Schedule set out in the Schedule to this Order for the Schedule to the 2000 Order (which was last substituted by the Immigration (Designation of Travel Bans) (Amendment) Order 2010 (“the 2010 Order”)) and has since been amended five times this year). Any person named by or under an instrument listed in the new Schedule or falling within a description in such an instrument will be excluded from the United Kingdom (subject to the exceptions specified in Article 3 of the 2000 Order).

title.div: The Mental Health (Independent Mental Health Advocates) (Wales) Regulations 2011 / Rheoliadau Iechyd Meddwl (Eiriolwyr Iechyd Meddwl Annibynnol) (Cymru) 2011

The Mental Health (Assessment of Former Users of Secondary Mental Health Services) (Wales) Regulations 2011 / Rheoliadau Iechyd Meddwl (Asesu Defnyddwyr Blaenorol o Wasanaethau Iechyd Meddwl Eilaidd) (Cymru) 2011
The Marketing of Fresh Horticultural Produce (Wales) (Amendment) Regulations 2011 / Rheoliadau Marchnata Cynnyrch Garddwriaethol Ffres (Cymru) (Diwygio) 2011

div.p: These Regulations give effect, in relation to Wales, to Commission Implementing Regulation (EU) No 543/2011 of 7 June 2011 laying down detailed rules for the application of Council Regulation (EC) No 1234/2007 in respect of the fruit and vegetables and processed fruit and vegetables sectors (OJ No L 157, 15.6.2011, p.1) “the Commission Implementing Regulation 543/2011”.

Mae'r Rheoliadau hyn yn rhoi effaith, o ran Cymru, i Reoliad Gweithredu'r Comisiwn (EU) Rhif 543/2011 dyddiedig 7 Mehefin 2011 sy'n gosod rheolau manwl ar gyfer cymhwyso Rheoliad y Cyngor (EC) Rhif 1234/2007 mewn perthynas â'r sectorau ffrwythau a llysiau a ffrwythau a llysiau wedi eu prosesu (OJ Rhif L 157, 15.6.2011, t.1) “Rheoliad Gweithredu'r Comisiwn 543/2011”.

entry.title: The Carriage of Dangerous Goods and Use of Transportable Pressure Equipment (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Carriage of Dangerous Goods and Use of Transportable Pressure Equipment Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2010 (“the 2010 Regulations”) in order to implement Directive 2010/35/EU of the European Parliament and the Council of 16 June 2010 on transportable pressure equipment and repealing Council Directives 76/767/EEC, 84/525/EEC, 84/526/EEC, 84/527/EEC and 1999/36/EC (OJ L165, 30.6.2010, p.1) (“the 2010 Directive”).

entry.title: The Airport Charges Regulations 2011
entry.summary: These Regulations implement Directive 2009/12/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of the European Union of 11th March 2009 on airport charges (“the Airport Charges Directive”).

title.div: The Housing (Wales) Measure 2011 (Commencement No. 1) Order 2011 / Gorchymyn Mesur Tai (Cymru) 2011 (Cychwyn Rhif 1) 2011

div.p: This Order, made by the Welsh Ministers, commences the majority of Part 2 (Registered Social Landlords) of the Housing (Wales) Measure 2011 (“the Measure”) on 18 October 2011 (“the first commencement date”) with the remainder coming into force on 2 December 2011 (“the second commencement date”).

Mae'r Gorchymyn hwn, a wnaed gan Weinidogion Cymru, yn cychwyn y rhan fwyaf o Ran 2 (Landlordiaid Cymdeithasol Cofrestredig) o Fesur Tai (Cymru) 2011 (“y Mesur”) ar 18 Hydref 2011 (“y dyddiad cychwyn cyntaf”) a'r gweddill yn dod i rym ar 2 Rhagfyr 2011 (“yr ail ddyddiad cychwyn”).
